{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778903950581,"sessionID":"ses_1d10fedfeffeABe5xPEWkT8L3l","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"functions.read:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"**Preferred term label:**\\nKidney Interpolar Region\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\nCentral Pole of Kidney\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nThis is already defined in NCIT: \\nKidney Interpolar Region\\nhttp://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C186124Copy\\n\\n**Parent term (use https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/uberon)**\\n\\n\\n**Your nano-attribution (ORCID)**\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n3:   \"comments\": [\n4:     {\n5:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87A-zih\",\n6:       \"author\": {\n7:         \"login\": \"taylordm\"\n8:       },\n9:       \"authorAssociation\": \"NONE\",\n10:       \"body\": \"Needed for dGTEx sampling of Kidney\",\n11:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-08-29T17:09:06Z\",\n12:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n13:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n14:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n15:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n16:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3237689505\",\n17:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n18:     },\n19:     {\n20:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87DlVwy\",\n21:       \"author\": {\n22:         \"login\": \"cmungall\"\n23:       },\n24:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n25:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please plan adding this term to Uberon. Look at the placement in NCIT, and find a good literature or textbook reference to use for the definition. Report findings on this issue before making a PR\",\n26:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-09-11T15:14:25Z\",\n27:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n28:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n29:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n30:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n31:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3281345586\",\n32:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n33:     },\n34:     {\n35:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87DlivQ\",\n36:       \"author\": {\n37:         \"login\": \"dragon-ai-agent\"\n38:       },\n39:       \"authorAssociation\": \"COLLABORATOR\",\n40:       \"body\": \"## Research Findings for Kidney Interpolar Region\\n\\n@dragon-ai-agent has completed the research for adding \\\"Kidney Interpolar Region\\\" to UBERON. Here are the comprehensive findings:\\n\\n### Anatomical Definition\\nThe **kidney interpolar region** (synonym: \\\"central pole of kidney\\\") is the middle portion of the kidney located between the upper and lower poles. It represents approximately the middle third of the kidney's longitudinal axis and is bounded by:\\n- Superior boundary: Upper pole of kidney\\n- Inferior boundary: Lower pole of kidney  \\n- Contains central portions of both renal cortex and medulla\\n\\n### NCIT Analysis\\n- NCIT term: C186124 \\\"Kidney Interpolar Region\\\"\\n- Already defined in NCIT with appropriate placement\\n- Used extensively in clinical radiology and pathology\\n\\n### Literature Support\\nFound strong literature support with multiple authoritative references:\\n- **Key PMIDs for definition**: PMID:25659322, PMID:28444432, PMID:15876515, PMID:32156458, PMID:27834214\\n- Widely used in medical imaging, surgical planning, and nephrology literature\\n- Established anatomical concept in human anatomy textbooks and clinical practice\\n\\n### Proposed UBERON Placement\\nBased on analysis of existing kidney anatomy terms in UBERON:\\n\\n**Parent class**: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part\\n- **Relationships**: \\n  - part_of UBERON:0002113 ! kidney\\n  - contributes_to_morphology_of UBERON:0002113 ! kidney\\n\\n**Logical definition pattern** (following existing kidney part patterns):\\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part  \\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002113 ! kidney\\n\\n### Current UBERON Status\\n- ✅ No conflicting terms found\\n- ✅ Fits well with existing kidney anatomy hierarchy\\n- ✅ Upper/lower pole terms don't currently exist (could be added later if needed)\\n- ✅ Clear relationships to existing terms like cortex of kidney, renal medulla\\n\\n### Recommendation\\n**Ready to proceed** with term creation. The research shows:\\n1. Strong anatomical... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n41:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-09-11T15:23:21Z\",\n42:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n43:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n44:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n45:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n46:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3281398736\",\n47:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n48:     },\n49:     {\n50:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87Dl24c\",\n51:       \"author\": {\n52:         \"login\": \"cmungall\"\n53:       },\n54:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n55:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please do it, with these modifications\\n\\n- don't include a logical definition. This is only for N+S conditions\\n- don't bother with the contributes_to_morphology_of. You are right that we have done this in the past, but let's keep it simple\\n- don't use any of these PMIDs\\n\\nCredit @taylordm her ORCID is https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3302-4610\",\n56:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-09-11T15:37:16Z\",\n57:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n58:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n59:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n60:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n61:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3281481244\",\n62:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n63:     },\n64:     {\n65:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87Dl_VK\",\n66:       \"author\": {\n67:         \"login\": \"dragon-ai-agent\"\n68:       },\n69:       \"authorAssociation\": \"COLLABORATOR\",\n70:       \"body\": \"## Implementation Progress\\n\\n@dragon-ai-agent has prepared the kidney interpolar region term with the requested modifications:\\n\\n### Term Details Created\\n- ID: UBERON:7770009 (next available in sequence)\\n- Name: kidney interpolar region\\n- Synonyms: \\n  - central pole of kidney (EXACT)\\n  - interpolar region of kidney (EXACT)\\n- Definition: The middle portion of the kidney situated between the upper pole and the lower pole, representing approximately the middle third of the kidney along its longitudinal axis. [Wikipedia:Kidney]\\n\\n### Applied Modifications per @cmungall\\n✅ No logical definition - Removed intersection_of axioms (only for N+S conditions)\\n✅ No contributes_to_morphology_of - Simplified relationships  \\n✅ No PMIDs - Using only Wikipedia reference as requested  \\n✅ Credited @taylordm - Added dc-contributor with ORCID 0000-0002-3302-4610  \\n\\n### Simplified Structure\\nis_a: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part\\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002113 ! kidney\\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3302-4610 ! Danielle Taylor\\n\\n### Next Steps\\nCurrently awaiting file edit permissions to add the term to src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo. Once permissions are granted, I will:\\n1. Insert the complete term definition\\n2. Commit the changes \\n3. Create a PR for review\\n\\nThe term is ready and follows all UBERON formatting standards and the specific requirements outlined.\\n\\n@dragon-ai-agent\",\n71:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-09-11T15:44:00Z\",\n72:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n73:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n74:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n75:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n76:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3281515850\",\n77:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n78:     },\n79:     {\n80:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87DnxOP\",\n81:       \"author\": {\n82:         \"login\": \"cmungall\"\n83:       },\n84:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n85:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please try again. My apologies, your permissions were not set correctly before. It should work now.\\n\\nAnd it's Deanne not Danielle\",\n86:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-09-11T17:23:09Z\",\n87:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n88:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n89:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n90:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n91:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3281982351\",\n92:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n93:     }\n94:   ],\n95:   \"title\": \"dGTEx terms needed in Uberon\",\n96:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604\"\n97: }\n\n(End of file - total 97 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"**Preferred term label:**\\nKidney Interpolar Region\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\nCentral Pole of Kidney\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nThis is already defined in NCIT: \\nKidney Interpolar Region\\nhttp://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C186124Copy\\n\\n**Parent term (use https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/uberon)**\\n\\n\\n**Your nano-attribution (ORCID)**\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n  \"comments\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87A-zih\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"taylordm\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"NONE\",\n      \"body\": \"Needed for dGTEx sampling of Kidney\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-08-29T17:09:06Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3237689505\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87DlVwy\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"__issue_context__.json","time":{"start":1778903950558,"end":1778903950579}},"id":"prt_e2ef0246e001zkc96kiCi8BTX0","sessionID":"ses_1d10fedfeffeABe5xPEWkT8L3l","messageID":"msg_e2ef01303001SlPQh7dPkbYicU"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778903950719,"sessionID":"ses_1d10fedfeffeABe5xPEWkT8L3l","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"functions.read:1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/AGENTS.md"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/AGENTS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # UBERON Ontology Project Guide\n2: \n3: This includes instructions for editing the uberon ontology. \n4: \n5: ## Project Layout\n6: - Main development file is `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n7: - individual terms checked out in `terms`\n8: - ODK and ontology documentation can be found in `/docs/`\n9: \n10: ## Querying ontology\n11: \n12: - To look at a specific term if you know the ID:\n13:     - `obo-grep.pl -r 'id: UBERON:0004177' src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n14: - All mentions of an ID\n15:     - `obo-grep.pl -r 'UBERON:0004177' src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n16: - Note that `obo-grep.pl` is in your PATH, no need to search for it    \n17: - Only search over `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n18: - DO NOT bother doing your own greps over the file, or looking for other files, unless otherwise asked, you will just waste time.\n19: - ONLY use the methods above for searching the ontology\n20: \n21: ## Before making edits\n22: - Read the request carefully and make a plan, especially if there is nuance\n23: - If related issues are mentioned read them: `gh issue view GITHUB-ISSUE-NUMBER`\n24: - if a PMID is mentioned in the issue, ALWAYS try and read it\n25: - ALWAYS check proposed parent terms for consistency\n26: - For terms that are compositional, check `src/patterns/dosdp-patterns/*.yaml`\n27: \n28: ## Editors guide\n29: - design patterns are in docs/patterns\n30: \n31: ## Edits\n32: - IMPORTANT: Do not edit the edit file directly, it's large\n33: - Add edits should be made in the `terms/` folder\n34: - check out a term into `terms/`: `obo-checkout.pl src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo UBERON:1234567 [OTHER IDS]`\n35: - This will create a single stanza obo files `terms/UBERON_1234567.obo` which you can easily edit\n36:      - (note the colon is replaced with an underscore)\n37: - You can go ahead and edit the smallers files in the `terms/` folder\n38: - After edits, check back in: `obo-checkin.pl src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo UBERON:1234567 [OTHER IDS]`\n39: - if you like you can edit multiple terms in one batch, e.g. `terms/my_batch.obo`\n40:      - `obo-checkout.pl src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo terms/my_batch.obo`\n41: - checking in will update the edit file and remove the file from `terms/`\n42: - before committing, src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo should be reserialised via `robot convert -i  src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo -f obo -o src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n43: - Commits are then made on src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo as appropriate\n44: - Note that `obo-checkin.pl` and `obo-checkout.pl` are in your PATH, no need to search for it\n45: - New terms must have:\n46:    - `relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/<ORCID> ! <NAME>`, where this is the person(s) in the issue\n47:    - `property_value: dcterms-date \"<ISO-TIMESTAMP>\" xsd:dateTime`\n48: \n49: \n50: \n51: ## OBO Format Guidelines\n52: - Term ID format: UBERON:NNNNNNN (7-digit number)\n53: - Handling New Term Requests (NTRs):\n54:   - New terms start  UBERON:99xxxxx\n55: - Each term requires: id, name, definition with references\n56: - Never guess UBERON IDs, or ontology term IDs, use search tools above to determine actual term\n57: - Never guess PMIDs for references, do a web search if needed\n58: - Use standard relationship types: is_a, part_of, has_part, etc.\n59: - Follow existing term patterns for consistency\n60: \n61: ## Publications\n62: - Run the command `aurelian fulltext <PMID:nnn>` to fetch full text for a publication. A doi or URL can also be used\n63: - You should cite publications appropriately, e.g. `def: \"....\" [PMID:nnnn, doi:mmmm]\n64: \n65: ## GitHub Contribution Process\n66: - most requests from users should follow one of two patterns:\n67:     - you are not confident how to proceed, in which case end with asking a clarifying question (via `gh`)\n68:     - you are confident how to proceed, you make changes, commit on a branch, and open a PR for the user to review\n69: - Check existing terms before adding new ones\n70: - For new terms: provide name, definition, place in hierarchy, and references\n71: - Include PMIDs for all assertions\n72: - Follow naming conventions from parent terms\n73: - always commit in a branch, e.g. issue-NNN\n74: - if there is an existing PR which you started then checkout that branch and continue, rather than starting a new PR (unless you explicitly want to abandon the original PR, e.g. it was on completely the wrong tracks)\n75: - always make clear detailed commit messages, saying what you did and why\n76: - always sign your commits `@dragon-ai-agent`\n77: - create PRs using `gh pr create ...`\n78: - File PRs with clear descriptions, and sign your PR\n79: \n80: ## Handling GitHub issues and requests\n81: - Use `gh` to read and write issues/PRs\n82: - Sign all commits and PRs as `@dragon-ai-agent`\n83: \n84: ## TROUBLESHOOTING\n85: - if your obo file has syntax errors, you can use `robot convert -vvv` to see full trace\n86: \n87: ## Obsoleting terms\n88: \n89: obsolete terms should have no logical axioms (is_a, relationship,\n90: intersection_of) on them. Obsolete terms may be replaced by a single\n91: term (so-called obsoletion with exact replacement), or by zero to many `consider` tags.\n92: \n93: \n94: Synonyms and xrefs can be migrated judiciously,\n95: \n96: We never do complete merges now, so there should be no `alt_ids` or\n97: disappearing stanzas. If a user asks for a merge, they usually mean\n98: obsoletion with direct replacement, as here:\n99: \n100: Example:\n101: \n102: ```\n103: [Term]\n104: id: UBERON:0001050\n105: name: obsolete atrium\n106: comment: obsoleted because 'atrium' as a general grouping class that encompasses the cardiac atrium and atrium of alveolus atrium is of questionable value. Furthermore, the use of the term 'atrium' in the generic sense is misleading, as this is commonly used to refer specifically to the cardiac atrium\n107: is_obsolete: true\n108: consider: FMA:85574\n109: consider: UBERON:0002081\n110: ```\n111: \n112: No relationship should point to an obsolete term - when you obsolete a term, you may need to also rewire\n113: terms to \"skip\" the obsoleted term.\n114: \n115: ## Other metadata\n116: \n117: - Link back to the issue you are dealing with using the `term_tracker_item`\n118: - All terms should have definitions, with at least one definition xref, ideally a PMID\n119: - You can sign terms as `created_by: dragon-ai-agent`\n120: \n121: ## Relationships\n122: \n123: All terms should have at least one `is_a` (this can be implicit by a logical definition, see below).\n124: Many terms in this ontology have part_of relationships.\n125: \n126: ## Logical definitions\n127: \n128: These should follow genus-differentia form, and the text definition should mirror the logical definition. Example:\n129: \n130: ```\n131: [Term]\n132: id: UBERON:0001742\n133: name: epiglottic cartilage\n134: def: \"The most superior of the laryngeal cartilages, which is found at the root of the tongue and folds back over the entrance to the larynx during swallowing.\" [MP:0002259]\n135: subset: uberon_slim\n136: xref: EMAPA:37522 {source=\"MA:th\"}\n137: xref: FMA:55112\n138: xref: MA:0001763\n139: xref: NCIT:C32526\n140: xref: SCTID:278990001\n141: xref: UMLS:C0458526 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Epiglottic_Cartilage\"}\n142: intersection_of: UBERON:0001739 ! laryngeal cartilage\n143: intersection_of: part_of UBERON:0000388 ! epiglottis\n144: relationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0001996 ! elastic cartilage tissue\n145: ```\n146: \n147: The reasoner can find the most specific `is_a`, so it's OK to leave this off.\n148: \n\n(End of file - total 148 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# UBERON Ontology Project Guide\n\nThis includes instructions for editing the uberon ontology. \n\n## Project Layout\n- Main development file is `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n- individual terms checked out in `terms`\n- ODK and ontology documentation can be found in `/docs/`\n\n## Querying ontology\n\n- To look at a specific term if you know the ID:\n    - `obo-grep.pl -r 'id: UBERON:0004177' src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n- All mentions of an ID\n    - `obo-grep.pl -r 'UBERON:0004177' src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n- Note that `obo-grep.pl` is in your PATH, no need to search for it    \n- Only search over `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n- DO NOT bother doing your own greps over the file, or looking for other files, unless otherwise asked, you will just waste time.\n- ONLY use the methods above for searching the ontology\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"AGENTS.md","time":{"start":1778903950712,"end":1778903950718}},"id":"prt_e2ef024f6001iyfOX5qWZpnWLB","sessionID":"ses_1d10fedfeffeABe5xPEWkT8L3l","messageID":"msg_e2ef01303001SlPQh7dPkbYicU"}}
